Pronunciation:
Notes: [Cf P: line, go (for a trip up the): To go to prison: 20 c (quot 1934).] used as euphemism for mental hospital in phrases (depending mainly on geographical location of observer). 1949 R. Mason. up the line in Porirua Mental Hospital, Wellington only; e.g. He has been up the line. -->1981 Feb Avondale College (Auckland) Slang Words in Use  (Goldie Brown Collection) down the line
